</table>

<h3>4.3 Services Page (services.html)</h3>
<p>Detailed breakdown of all six service categories with rich SVG illustrations.</p>

<h4>Services:</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Service</th><th>SVG Illustration</th></tr>
  <tr><td>01</td><td>Software Development &amp; Products</td><td>Monitor with code editor, mobile phone, and code brackets</td></tr>
  <tr><td>02</td><td>Cybersecurity Services</td><td>Shield with checkmark, security nodes, NDPR/GDPR badge</td></tr>
  <tr><td>03</td><td>Hardware Configuration &amp; Infrastructure</td><td>Server rack with LED status lights and network connections</td></tr>
  <tr><td>04</td><td>Cloud Computing Services</td><td>Cloud with IaaS/PaaS/SaaS cards, AWS/Azure/GCP badges</td></tr>
  <tr><td>05</td><td>ICT Training &amp; Education</td><td>Laptop with video call, course content, certification badge</td></tr>
  <tr><td>06</td><td>IT Consulting &amp; Advisory</td><td>Strategy board with roadmap timeline and growth chart</td></tr>
</table>

<p>The page also includes a Products section with all 7 original products, a Testimonials section with 3 client reviews, and a CTA banner.</p>

<h3>4.4 Products Page (products.html)</h3>
<p>The most comprehensive page, featuring all 10 software products with interactive UI mockups, feature chips, and demo CTAs.</p>

<h4>Features:</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Sticky product navigation bar</strong> &mdash; Scrollable pill-nav that highlights the active product section as the user scrolls</li>
  <li><strong>Alternating layouts</strong> &mdash; Products alternate between left-visual/right-info and reversed layouts</li>
  <li><strong>CSS-only UI mockups</strong> &mdash; Each product has a simulated app interface with coloured sidebars, toolbars, stat cards, charts, and tables</li>
  <li><strong>Feature chips</strong> &mdash; Pill-shaped tags listing key features for each product</li>
  <li><strong>"Why Thrive Products"</strong> &mdash; Dark section with 6 advantage cards</li>
</ul>

<h3>4.5 Contact Page (contact.html)</h3>
<p>Provides contact information and a functional form connected to the backend server.</p>

<h4>Sections:</h4>
<table>
  <tr><th>Section</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Contact Info</td><td>Head Office address (Abuja), email, phone number, business hours</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Contact Form</td><td>7 fields: First Name*, Last Name*, Email*, Phone, Company, Service Interest (dropdown), Message*. Connected to /api/contact endpoint</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Our Headquarters</td><td>Single office card for Abuja, Nigeria (HQ)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Map Placeholder</td><td>Placeholder section for future interactive map integration</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>4.6 Admin Dashboard (admin.html)</h3>
<p>A protected dashboard page for viewing and managing contact form submissions.</p>

<h4>Features:</h4>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Stats cards</strong> &mdash; Total submissions, unread count, today's submissions</li>
  <li><strong>Submissions table</strong> &mdash; Status badge (New/Read), name, email, service, date, actions</li>
  <li><strong>View detail modal</strong> &mdash; Full submission details including message content</li>
  <li><strong>Delete functionality</strong> &mdash; Remove submissions with confirmation</li>
  <li><strong>Auto-mark as read</strong> &mdash; Submissions are marked as read when viewed</li>
  <li><strong>Refresh button</strong> &mdash; Reload data without page refresh</li>
</ul>

