<!-- ============ 7. BACKEND & API ============ -->
<h2>7. Backend &amp; API</h2>

<h3>7.1 Server Configuration</h3>
<p>The backend is built with Node.js and Express 5.2, running on port 4000 by default. It serves all static website files and provides a RESTful API for contact form submissions.</p>

<div class="code">File: server.js
Port: 4000
Database: data/submissions.db (SQLite)
Dependencies: express, better-sqlite3, cors</div>

<h3>7.2 API Endpoints</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Method</th><th>Endpoint</th><th>Description</th><th>Auth Required</th></tr>
  <tr><td>POST</td><td>/api/contact</td><td>Submit a new contact form entry</td><td>No</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/submissions</td><td>Retrieve all submissions (newest first)</td><td>No*</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/submissions/:id</td><td>View a single submission (marks as read)</td><td>No*</td></tr>
  <tr><td>DELETE</td><td>/api/submissions/:id</td><td>Delete a submission</td><td>No*</td></tr>
  <tr><td>GET</td><td>/api/stats</td><td>Get total, unread, and today's counts</td><td>No*</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="warning"><strong>Note:</strong> Endpoints marked with * should have authentication added before deploying to production. Currently they are open for development purposes.</div>

<h3>7.3 POST /api/contact Request Body</h3>
<div class="code">{
  "firstName": "John",        // Required
  "lastName": "Doe",          // Required
  "email": "john@company.com", // Required (validated)
  "phone": "+234 800 000",    // Optional
  "company": "Company Ltd",   // Optional
  "service": "software",      // Optional
  "message": "Hello..."       // Required
}</div>

<h3>7.4 Success Response</h3>
<div class="code">{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Thank you! Your message has been received...",
  "id": 1
}</div>

<!-- ============ 8. DATABASE SCHEMA ============ -->
<h2>8. Database Schema</h2>

<h3>Table: submissions</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th><th>Description</th></tr>
  <tr><td>id</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>PRIMARY KEY, AUTOINCREMENT</td><td>Unique submission ID</td></tr>
  <tr><td>first_name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td><td>Submitter's first name</td></tr>
  <tr><td>last_name</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td><td>Submitter's last name</td></tr>
  <tr><td>email</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td><td>Submitter's email address</td></tr>
  <tr><td>phone</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NULLABLE</td><td>Phone number</td></tr>
  <tr><td>company</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NULLABLE</td><td>Company or organisation name</td></tr>
  <tr><td>service</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NULLABLE</td><td>Service of interest</td></tr>
  <tr><td>message</td><td>TEXT</td><td>NOT NULL</td><td>Message content</td></tr>
  <tr><td>submitted_at</td><td>DATETIME</td><td>DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP</td><td>Date and time of submission</td></tr>
  <tr><td>is_read</td><td>INTEGER</td><td>DEFAULT 0</td><td>Read status (0 = unread, 1 = read)</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ============ 9. HOW TO RUN ============ -->
<h2>9. How to Run the Website</h2>

<h3>9.1 Prerequisites</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Node.js (version 18 or higher) installed on the system</li>
  <li>npm (comes with Node.js)</li>
</ul>

<h3>9.2 First-Time Setup</h3>
<div class="code">1. Open a terminal/command prompt
2. Navigate to the project folder:
   cd "C:\Users\ZEUS\Desktop\ThriveCore Technologies"

3. Install dependencies:
   npm install

4. Start the server:
   npm start</div>

<h3>9.3 Accessing the Site</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Page</th><th>URL</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Home Page</td><td>http://localhost:4000</td></tr>
  <tr><td>About Page</td><td>http://localhost:4000/about.html</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Services Page</td><td>http://localhost:4000/services.html</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Products Page</td><td>http://localhost:4000/products.html</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Contact Page</td><td>http://localhost:4000/contact.html</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Admin Dashboard</td><td>http://localhost:4000/admin</td></tr>
</table>

<div class="note"><strong>Important:</strong> The contact form only works when the site is accessed through the server (http://localhost:4000). Opening HTML files directly in the browser will not connect to the backend.</div>

<!-- ============ 10. DEPLOYMENT GUIDE ============ -->
<h2>10. Deployment Guide</h2>

<h3>10.1 Option A: VPS / Cloud Server (Recommended)</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Provision a server (e.g., DigitalOcean, AWS EC2, or Azure VM)</li>
  <li>Install Node.js on the server</li>
  <li>Upload all project files to the server</li>
  <li>Run <code>npm install</code> to install dependencies</li>
  <li>Use PM2 to keep the server running: <code>npm install -g pm2 &amp;&amp; pm2 start server.js</code></li>
  <li>Configure Nginx as a reverse proxy to forward port 80/443 to port 4000</li>
  <li>Set up SSL certificate using Let's Encrypt for HTTPS</li>
  <li>Point your domain (e.g., thrivecoretech.com) to the server IP</li>
</ol>

<h3>10.2 Option B: Static Hosting + Separate Backend</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Deploy the HTML/CSS/JS files to a static host (Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Pages)</li>
  <li>Deploy the Node.js backend to a service like Render, Railway, or Heroku</li>
  <li>Update the API URL in main.js to point to the backend URL</li>
</ol>

<h3>10.3 Pre-Deployment Checklist</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Add authentication to admin dashboard and API endpoints</li>
  <li>Update contact email and phone number to real values</li>
  <li>Replace placeholder social media links with actual URLs</li>
  <li>Add real team member names and photos to the About page</li>
  <li>Configure environment variables for production port</li>
  <li>Set up database backups for submissions.db</li>
  <li>Add rate limiting to the contact API to prevent spam</li>
  <li>Test all pages on multiple devices and browsers</li>
</ul>

<!-- ============ 11. MAINTENANCE ============ -->
<h2>11. Maintenance &amp; Updates</h2>

<h3>11.1 Adding a New Product</h3>
<p>To add a new product to the website, update the following files:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>products.html</strong> &mdash; Add a nav item in the product navigation bar and a full product section with mockup</li>
  <li><strong>index.html</strong> &mdash; Add a product card in the products grid section</li>
  <li><strong>All 5 HTML files</strong> &mdash; Add the product to the footer products list</li>
  <li><strong>about.html</strong> &mdash; Update the "Software Products" counter data-target value</li>
</ol>

<h3>11.2 Updating Company Information</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Address/Location</strong> &mdash; Search for "Abuja" across all HTML files and update as needed</li>
  <li><strong>Phone/Email</strong> &mdash; Search for "info@thrivecoretech.com" and "+234 123 456 7890"</li>
  <li><strong>Copyright Year</strong> &mdash; Search for "&copy; 2026" in all footer sections</li>
</ul>

<h3>11.3 Changing Colours</h3>
<p>All colours are defined as CSS custom properties in the <code>:root</code> selector at the top of <code>css/styles.css</code>. Modify the variables there and they will cascade throughout the entire site.</p>

<h3>11.4 Backing Up the Database</h3>
<p>The SQLite database is a single file located at <code>data/submissions.db</code>. To back up, simply copy this file to a secure location. This can be automated with a scheduled task or cron job.</p>

